Included in this post is a form to make sure all students needing meals during our blended learning phase OR in case of school closure (going full remote) get those meals.

This will make sure our food service staff is getting enough food ordered and will be prepared to meet those needs in either case.

Of course families can call in to the school if they change their minds or opt out.

For instance, the ICGS teachers will hand out meals only to those signed up, so it’s important to be on this list to prevent bus delays etc.

If you have any questions, please call the school 217-482-5180 or send an email to illinicentral@illinicentral.org

#WeAreIC

post_text:
Good morning! We sent out paper copies of student schedule on Friday, so watch your mailbox! Schedules are also available on Skyward. All schedule change requests should be emailed to schedulechange@illinicentral.org. We are working to limit class sizes to maintain social distancing, so requests are not guaranteed. SCHEDULE CHANGES WILL NOT BE ALLOWED AFTER AUGUST 24TH.

We shared the Commitment to Graduation ceremony video last week, and we will not be able to hold in-person orientations or open house, so watch the website and facebook for information regarding these events happening digitally.

We are excited to start another school, as unique as it will be!

The regular meeting of the Illini Central CUSD #189 Board of Education will be held in person this month.

The meeting will be held on Thursday, July 16, 2020 at 7:00 pm. It will take place in the grade school library.
The meeting will be limited to 50 in-person attendees.

The Board and school personnel will account for at least 12 attendees. The district will broadcast the meeting through the Illini Central Sports Network.

Here is the link to the broadcast:
https://www.nfhsnetwork.com/events/illini-central-high-school-mason-city-il/evt9442ae4a7e

All in-person attendees will be required to wear a facemask per IDPH guidelines.

The agenda can be viewed at this link: https://v3.boardbook.org/Public/PublicHome.aspx?ak=1001831 or at the district’s website.

This is the first in-person meeting of the Board since March 12.

post_text:
Illini Central staff have begun planning to reopen schools for the 2020-2021 school year. Last week, the district received guidance from the Illinois State Board of Education that establishes both mandates and recommendations. That guidance recommends that schools plan for at least three possible scenarios. These include in-person learning with proper social distancing, a blended system that includes both in-person and remote aspects, and extended remote learning in the event of a surge in cases of Coronavirus.

The leadership team at IC is looking for input from the community to help guide the planning process. The families of students are asked to complete a brief survey to assist the district in its efforts. The survey is open through Sunday, July 5th.

Here is the link to the survey:

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScnWyLv6ArGMD7qcZ4SaWKBgR-rcQv6qspFzqlMgIiWDjesnQ/viewform

The district hopes to release a plan on or before July 24.

Thank you for your assistance & take care.

#WeAreIC

post_text:

The 1st State Bank of Mason City and Illini Central High School are pleased to present William Wise with the March Student of the Month Award. For demonstrating outstanding character, William receives a Barnes & Noble gift card from 1st State Bank and an Amazon gift card from the Illini Central High School faculty.

William is the son of James and Jenny Wise.

His classes this year include Advanced Biology, Advanced Chemistry, Research Management, AP Calculus, Physics, and Dual Credit English.

Outside of school, William is a part of the Mason City Swim Team.

William plans to attend Southern Illinois University-Carbondale, where he will major in Physiology.

Congratulations, William and thank you for all of your contributions to Illini Central during your high school years!

#WeAreIC

Illini Central CUSD #189 is recognizing the commitment of our substitutes by increasing daily compensation to $110. We are always looking for substitute coverage.

If you are interested in being added to our substitute list, please contact Kirsten Parr at 217-482-5180, extension 1141 or by email, kparr@illinicentral.org.

post_text:
Illini Central High School Principal Jennifer Durbin is pleased to announce that four students from Illini Central’s graduating class of 2020 have been recognized as Illinois State Scholars.

The Illinois Student Assistance Commission confers this prestigious recognition to top Illinois high school students annually. The 2020-2021 Illinois State Scholars represent approximately the top ten percent of high school seniors from 726 high schools across the state. The scholars are chosen based on exceptional ACT or SAT test scores and the scholars’ class rank at the end of their junior year.

The following Illini Central students are Illinois State Scholars:
Kyndal P. Arthalony daughter of Brent Arthalony and Teresa and Jason Harrison
Alexander R. Entwistle son of Scott and Kimberly Entwistle
Carter R. Martin son of Kirk and Tammy Martin
Grace K. Ratliff daughter of Michael and Stephanie Ratliff

“On behalf of Illini Central, we congratulate these students who have consistently shown focus, organization, and dedication to both their school and community,” said Mrs. Durbin.

#WeAreIC
